    question: 'Semaglutide vs Tirzepatide: which is right for me?',
    answer:
      'Both are once-weekly injections that reduce appetite and support weight loss. Tirzepatide activates two gut-hormone pathways (GIP and GLP-1) while Semaglutide activates one (GLP-1), and in studies Tirzepatide has produced greater average weight loss for many patients. The best choice depends on your health history, goals, budget, and how you respond, and Dr. Menon will help you decide.',
